OL,6,FHe also said he "doesn't read" hate
OL,7,Fcomments, adding "we live in a world
OL,8,Fwhere social media encourages people
OL,9,Fonly ever to speak to people who
OL,10,Fbelieves the same things as they do.
OL,11,F(It) never allows people to have a
OL,12,Fdialogue with someone who may take a
OL,13,Fdifferent point of view.
OL,15,F"I think Wales is a lot nicer and a
OL,16,Fkinder place than you might imagine if
OL,17,Fyou took your picture of it simply
OL,18,Ffrom the keyboard warriors who play
OL,19,Fout their particular and often very
OL,20,Fextreme views in that narrow world of
OL,21,Fsocial media."
